<p>July 20, 2012<br /><strong>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</strong><br />
  Contact: Julie Hertzog 952-838-9000, <a href="mailto:julie.hertzog@PACER.org"><strong>julie.hertzog@PACER.org</strong></a></p>
<h2><strong>PACER spokesperson Kylie Morgan performs with Jason Aldean in her national television debut July 23 on E!</strong></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:normal;background:white;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">Seventeen-year-old Kylie Morgan,  whose story and music are featured on PACER&rsquo;s </span><a href="http://www.pacerteensagainstbullying.org/#/act/speaking-out/kylie-morgan"><strong><span style="font-size:12.0pt; ">TeensAgainstBullying</span></strong></a><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; "> website, will make her national television debut Monday, July 23.  The Land Run recording artist from Newcastle, Okla., will open for country  music megastar Jason Aldean on the new reality show &ldquo;Opening Act.&rdquo; The program  airs at 10 p.m. Eastern, 9 p.m. Central on E! Entertainment Television.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:normal;background:white;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s the opportunity I have been  waiting for forever,&rdquo; said Kylie, who is a spokesperson for PACER&rsquo;s National  Bullying Prevention Center. &ldquo;I have been a big fan of Jason&rsquo;s, so when I found  out I would be opening for him it was a dream come true.&rdquo;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:normal;background:white;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">Kylie has been delivering her bullying  prevention message to audiences across the country. Now she will tell her story  to 80 million E! subscribers nationwide. &ldquo;</span><span style="color:black; ">PACER has been a great organization  that I have cared about for a long time,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;I talked about my bullying  prevention campaign &quot;It Matters What We Do&quot; on the show&nbsp;and my  work with PACER</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">.&rdquo;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:normal;background:white;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">&ldquo;Opening Act&rdquo; was developed by Nigel  Lythgoe, creator of the hit reality show &ldquo;American Idol.&rdquo; Producers scour the  Internet to find undiscovered talent on You Tube, and chosen performers have  the opportunity to open for a major star in a live concert. Kylie was flown to  Nashville where she had just five days to prepare for her big break. &ldquo;The idea  of the show is to take someone from singing in their bedroom to a huge stage  and give them the opportunity of a lifetime,&rdquo; Kylie said. &ldquo;There were no  auditions, no judges, no contests. That&rsquo;s what&rsquo;s great about the show &mdash; it&rsquo;s  different.&rdquo;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:normal;background:white;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">On &ldquo;Opening Act&rdquo; Kylie performs  &ldquo;Phoebe,&rdquo; a song she wrote about a teen who committed suicide after being bullied.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:normal;background:white;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">&ldquo;We are just so happy for Kylie. She  has been such a great supporter of PACER&rsquo;s work and has done so much to help  prevent bullying,&rdquo; said Julie Hertzog, Director of PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying  Prevention Center. &ldquo;Now she is carrying the message of hope to millions of  people.&rdquo;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:normal;background:white;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt; color:black; ">For more information on the work of  PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center, visit PACER.org/bullying. To learn  more about Kylie Morgan, visit KylieMorgan.com.</span></p>
